
  Name:  setbuf
  
  #include <stdio.h>
  void setbuf(FILE *stream, char *buf);
  
  The setbuf( ) function specifies the buffer that stream will use 
  or, if called with buf set to null, turns off buffering. If a 
  programmer-defined buffer is to be specified, it must be BUFSIZ 
  characters long.BUFSIZ is defined in <stdio.h> .
  
  Example:
  char buffer[BUFSIZ];
  ·
  ·
  ·
  setbuf(fp, buffer);

